HEADWORD: Hecatomb
<hw>Hec"a*tomb</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hecatombe</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ hundred + <?/ ox: cf. F.
<ets>h⟦eacute⟧catombe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A sacrifice
of a hundred oxen or cattle at the same time; hence, the sacrifice or
slaughter of any large number of victims.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Slaughtered <qex>hecatombs</qex> around them bleed.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More than a human <qex>hecatomb</qex>.</q>
